logspot.com/2010/10/catch-circa-1954.html |via=The Glory of Baseball |accessdate=May 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath and response==\n[[Image:MAYS THE CATCH.JPG|thumb|right|The baseball glove that Willie Mays used in \"the catch\" on display at the [[National Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum]] in 2008.]]\nThe play prevented the Indians from taking the lead and, in the bottom of the 10th, the Giants won the game on their way to sweeping the Series. The Catch is often considered to be one of the best and most memorable plays in the history of baseball because of the difficulty of the play and the importance of the game itself.<ref>{{cite news|last=Axisa|first=Mike|title=Happy 60th Anniversary: Willie Mays makes 'The Catch'|url=http://www.cbssports.com/mlb/news/happy-60th-anniversary-willie-mays-makes-the-catch/|publisher=[[CBS Sports]]|date=September 29, 2014|accessdate=June 22, 2016}}</ref>\n\nMays himself did not believe \"The Catch\" to be the best defensive play he ever made.<ref>{{cite news |last=Morgan |first=Joe |author-link=Joe Morgan |title=Mays was Mr. Everything |url=http://static.espn.go.com/mlb/columns/morgan_joe/1191373.html |publisher=[[ESPN.com]] |date=May 4, 2001 |accessdate=June 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite newspaper |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/10876935/not_my_top_catch_mays/ |title=Not My Top Catch \u2013 Mays |newspaper=[[Long Beach Independent]] |location=[[Long Beach, California]] |agency=[[United Press International|UPI]] |date=September 30, 1954 |accessdate=May 9, 2017 |via=newspapers.com}}</ref> In the CD collection ''[[Ernie Harwell]]'s Audio Scrapbook'', issued in 2006,<ref>{{cite book |first=Ernie |last=Harwell |author-link=Ernie Harwell |title=Ernie Harwell's Audio Scrapbook |publisher=AudioBook Publishing, LLC |date=November 15, 2006 |isbn=978-0979212000 |url=https://www.amazon.com/Ernie-Harwells-Audio-Scrapbook-Harwell/dp/0979212006/}}</ref> Mays talks about a running ''bare-handed'' catch he made at [[Forbes Field]] in [[Pittsburgh]] in 1951, in which the Giants' players teased the young rookie by treating him with complete indifference when he returned to the bench.{{cn|date=September 2019}} Mays also cited a catch he made against the center field wall at [[Ebbets Field]] in [[Brooklyn|Brooklyn, New York]], in which he had to scurry back so fast he did not have time to turn around.{{cn|date=September 2019}} Other observers have noted that Mays' quick relay throw from deep center field was the most important part of the 1954 play, the catch itself being merely a matter of Mays outrunning the ball.{{cn|date=September 2019}}\n\nIn 2007, a [[physicist]] calculated that if the temperature had been {{convert|77|F|C}} rather than {{convert|76|F|C}}, the ball would have traveled {{convert|2|in|cm}} farther than it did, and The Catch might not have been completed.<ref name=\"npr\">{{cite news|title=Engineering in the News March 2007 |url=http://www.engr.uiuc.edu/news/archive/index.php?xId=070208640700 |publisher=[[UIUC College of Engineering]] |date=March 2007 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070919035430/http://www.engr.uiuc.edu/news/archive/index.php?xId=070208640700 |archivedate=September 19, 2007 |accessdate=June 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.si.com/vault/2007/03/12/8402407/going-going-green |title=Going, Going Green |first=Alexander |last=Wolff |magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]] |date=March 12, 2007 |via=''Sports Illustrated'' Vault |accessdate=May 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.sportingnews.com/baseball/25moments/9.html |title=Baseball's 25 Greatest Moments \u2013 No. 9 The Catch |website=[[The Sporting News]] |date=1999 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/19991013122825/http://www.sportingnews.com/baseball/25moments/9.html |archive-date=October 13, 1999 |via=archive.org}}\n*{{cite web |url=http://www.time.com/time/2003/worldseries/moments/7.html |title=World 